resps:
The constraints fix several linked groups, but they do not determine a unique full grid. For example, Jack must be the Blue-house Fish owner who drinks Tea and is the Artist, while Emma is the Red-house Hamster owner with Dancing. The remaining roles can be completed in more than one way.

One valid complete assignment satisfying every constraint is:

Answer: {"Emma":{"HouseColor":"Red","Pet":"Hamster","Drink":"Soda","Job":"Chef","Hobby":"Dancing"},"Jack":{"HouseColor":"Blue","Pet":"Fish","Drink":"Tea","Job":"Artist","Hobby":"Hiking"},"Mike":{"HouseColor":"Yellow","Pet":"Rabbit","Drink":"Milk","Job":"Pilot","Hobby":"Gaming"},"Frank":{"HouseColor":"Purple","Pet":"Bird","Drink":"Coffee","Job":"Doctor","Hobby":"Sports"},"Kevin":{"HouseColor":"White","Pet":"Parrot","Drink":"Smoothie","Job":"Engineer","Hobby":"Painting"},"Alice":{"HouseColor":"Green","Pet":"Cat","Drink":"Lemonade","Job":"Nurse","Hobby":"Cooking"}}

The clues force Iris to be the Painting/Engineer/Black/Cat/Tea person, Grace to be the Artist/Milk/Dog person, and Mike to be the Blue/Lemonade/Nurse/Gaming person. Alice must be Purple/Doctor/Water/Parrot; otherwise the remaining drink-pet constraints conflict.  

The puzzle is slightly underdetermined: Laura and Emma can swap the Yellow/Bird/Soda/Lawyer profile with the Green/Hamster/Smoothie/Chef/Reading profile, and some remaining hobbies are interchangeable. Below is one valid completion satisfying every clue.

Answer: {"Alice":{"HouseColor":"Purple","Pet":"Parrot","Drink":"Water","Job":"Doctor","Hobby":"Dancing"},"Laura":{"HouseColor":"Yellow","Pet":"Bird","Drink":"Soda","Job":"Lawyer","Hobby":"Cooking"},"Emma":{"HouseColor":"Green","Pet":"Hamster","Drink":"Smoothie","Job":"Chef","Hobby":"Reading"},"Grace":{"HouseColor":"Red","Pet":"Dog","Drink":"Milk","Job":"Artist","Hobby":"Hiking"},"Mike":{"HouseColor":"Blue","Pet":"Turtle","Drink":"Lemonade","Job":"Nurse","Hobby":"Gaming"},"Iris":{"HouseColor":"Black","Pet":"Cat","Drink":"Tea","Job":"Engineer","Hobby":"Painting"}}

The constraints force David to be the Black-house Cat owner with Juice, Doctor, and Gaming. Bob must be the White-house Dog owner with Pilot and Hiking. The Purple/Artist/Rabbit/Coffee/Dancing set and the Red/Engineer/Bird set can then be assigned consistently among the remaining people.

The puzzle is not uniquely determined by the clues, but the following is one valid complete solution satisfying all constraints.

Answer: {"David":{"HouseColor":"Black","Pet":"Cat","Drink":"Juice","Job":"Doctor","Hobby":"Gaming"},"Emma":{"HouseColor":"Purple","Pet":"Rabbit","Drink":"Coffee","Job":"Artist","Hobby":"Dancing"},"Jack":{"HouseColor":"Red","Pet":"Bird","Drink":"Smoothie","Job":"Engineer","Hobby":"Reading"},"Carol":{"HouseColor":"Orange","Pet":"Fish","Drink":"Lemonade","Job":"Nurse","Hobby":"Painting"},"Laura":{"HouseColor":"Blue","Pet":"Hamster","Drink":"Milk","Job":"Lawyer","Hobby":"Sports"},"Bob":{"HouseColor":"White","Pet":"Dog","Drink":"Water","Job":"Pilot","Hobby":"Hiking"}}
